The '''March 2007 audio rework''' was a major rework of ''[[RuneScape 2|RuneScape]]''’s [[music]] player that was [[Update:The Feldip Hills are alive with the sound of muuuusic!|released]] on [[6 March]] [[2007]]. As part of this rework, all of ''RuneScape''’s existing songs were updated with new recording technology. 

When the [[Music player]] was first released on [[15 March]] [[2004]], the game's songs sounded significantly different than they do today. The music player was dependent on the soundcards of individual players' computers to play the tracks, making songs more digital-sounding and less like actual musical instruments were used in them. To address this, the music player was completely reworked in early 2007 - from March 2007 onwards, songs were created using a bank of instruments built into the game itself.<ref>[[Update:The Feldip Hills are alive with the sound of muuuusic!]]</ref> All existing songs (456 at the time of the update) were updated to better reflect the new music player's sound. ''[[Old School RuneScape]]'' uses the music system derived from the audio rework.

The last music tracks released prior to the rework were [[Creature Cruelty]], [[Magic, Magic, Magic]], [[Mutant Medley]], and [[Work, Work, Work]], all as part of the [[Tower of Life]] quest on [[19 February]] 2007. The first music track released after the rework was [[Zombiism]], alongside [[The Great Brain Robbery]] on the same day of the music update.

The original versions of each song can be found under the "Versions" section of articles for music tracks released prior to March 2007.

